Severe Weather Drill ... 18 \n1.5.5 Training Practices ... 19 \n1.5.6 ERCOT Operator Certification Program ... 19 \n2 System Operations and Control Requirements ... 1 \n2.1 Operational Duties ... 1 \n2.2 System Monitoring and Control ... 3 \n2.2.1 Overview ... 3 \n2.2.2 Security Criteria ... 5 \n2.2.3 Response to Transient Voltage Disturbance ... 5 \n2.2.4 Load Frequency Control ... 5 \n2.2.4.1 Maintenance and Verification ... 6 \n2.2.4.2 Regulation Provider Loss of AGC ... 6 \n2.2.4.3 ERCOT Loss of AGC ... 7 \n2.2.5 Automatic Voltage Regulators ... 7 \n2.2.6 Power System Stabilizers ... 10 \n2.2.7 Turbine Speed Governors ... 12 \n2.2.8 Performance/Disturbance/Compliance Analysis ... 13 \n2.2.9 Time Error and Time Synchronization ... 14 \n2.2.9.1 Time Error ... 14 \n2.2.9.2 Time Synchronization ... 14 \n2.2.10 Generation Resource and Energy Storage Resource Response Time Requirements ... 15 \n2.3 Ancillary Services ... 16 \n2.3.1 Responsive Reserve ... 24 \n2.3.1.1 Obligation ... 24 \n2.3.1.2 Additional Operational Details for Responsive Reserve Provders ... 24 \n2.3.1.2.1 Limit on Generation Resources and Controllable Load Resources Providing \nRRS ... 30 \n2.3.2 Non-Spinning Reserve Service ... 31 \n2.3.2.1 Additional Operational Details for Non-Spinning Reserve Service Providers ... 31 \n\nERCOT NODAL OPERATING GUIDES – APRIL 1, 2024 3 \n2.3.3 ERCOT Contigency Reserve Service ... 33 \n2.3.3.1 Additional Operational Details for ERCOT Contigency Reserve Service (ECRS) \nProviders ... 33 \n2.4 Outage Coordination ... 35 \n2.5 Reliability Unit Commitment ... 36 \n2.5.1 Criteria for Removing Contingencies from the RUC Analyses ... 36 \n2.6 Requirements for Under-Frequency and Over- Frequency Relaying ... 36 \n2.6.1 Automatic Firm Load Shedding ... 36 \n2.6.2 Generators and Energy Storage Resources ... 40 \n2.6.2.1 Frequency Ride-Through Requirements for Distribution Generation Resources (DGRs) \nand Distribution Energy Storage Resources (DESRs) ... 40 \n2.6.3 Frequency Ride-Through Requirements for Direct Current Ties (DC Ties) ... 41 \n2.7 System Voltage Profile and Operational Voltage Control ... 42 \n2.7.1 Introduction ... 42 \n2.7.2 Maintaining Voltage Profile ... 42 \n2.7.3 Real-Time Operational Voltage Control ... 45 \n2.7.3.1 Operational Guidelines ... 45 \n2.7.3.2 ERCOT Responsibilities ... 46 \n2.7.3.3 TO/TSP Responsibilities ... 47 \n2.7.3.4 QSE Responsibilities ... 49 \n2.7.3.5 Resource Entity Responsibilities and Generation Resource and Energy Storage \nResource Requirements ... 50 \n2.7.4 Special Consideration for Nuclear Power Plants ... 52 \n2.7.5 Parameters for Standard Reactor and Capacitor Switching Plan ... 52 \n2.7.6 Unit Dispatch Beyond the Corrected Unit Reactive Limit or Unit Reactive Limit ... 53 \n2.8 Operation of Direct Current Ties ... 53 \n2.8.1 Inadvertent Energy Management ... 54 \n2.9 Voltage Ride-Through Requirements For Generation Resources and Energy Storage Resources.54 \n2.9.1 Voltage Ride-Through Requirements for Intermittent Renewable Resources and Energy \nStorage Resources Connected to the ERCOT Transmission Grid ... 56 \n2.9.2 Voltage Ride-Through Requirements for Distribution Generation Resources (DGRs) and \nDistribution Energy Storage Resources (DESRs) ... 58 \n2.10 Voltage Ride-Through Requirements For DC Ties ... 59 \n3 ERCOT AND MARKET PARTICIPANT RESPONSIBILITIES ... 1 \n3.1 System Control Interfaces with ERCOT ... 1 \n3.1.1 Introduction ... 1 \n3.1.2 Compliance with Dispatch Instructions ... 1 \n3.1.3 Dispatch Instructions ... 1 \n3.2 Qualified Scheduling Entities ... 3 \n3.2.1 Operating Obligations ... 3 \n3.2.2 Changes in Resource Status ... 4 \n3.2.3 Regulatory Required Incident and Disturbance Reports ... 4 \n3.2.4 Ancillary Service Qualification and Testing Program ... 5 \n3.3 Resource Entities ... 6 \n3.3.1 Unit Capability Requirements ... 9 \n3.3.2 Unit Reactive Capability Requirements ... 10 \n3.3.3 Resource Entity Responsibilities for Equipment Ratings ... 17 \n3.4 Load Resource Testing Requirement ... 18 \n3.5 ERCOT Implementation ... 18 \n3.6 Transmission Service Providers ... 19 \n3.7 Transmission Operators ... 19 \n3.7.1 Transmission Owner Responsibility for a Vegetation Management Program ... 22 \n3.7.2 Trasmission Service Provider Responsibilities for Equipment Ratings ... 22 \n3.8 Requirements for Reporting Sabotage Information ... 23 \n\nERCOT NODAL OPERATING GUIDES – APRIL 1, 2024 4 \n4 Emergency Operations ... 2 \n4.1 Introduction ... 2 \n4.2 Communication Under Emergency Conditions ... 2 \n4.2.1 Operating Condition Notice ... 2 \n4.2.2 Advisory ... 3 \n4.2.3 Watch ... 4 \n4.2.4 Emergency Notice ... 5 \n4.3 Operation to Maintain Transmission System Security ... 5 \n4.3.1 Real-Time and Short Term Planning ... 6 \n4.4 Block Load Transfers between ERCOT and Non-ERCOT System ... 6 \n4.5 Energy Emergency Alert (EEA) ... 6 \n4.5.1 General ... 6 \n4.5.2 Operating Procedures ... 7 \n4.5.3 Implementation ... 9 \n4.5.3.1 General Procedures Prior to EEA Operations ... 11 \n4.5.3.2 General Procedures During EEA Operations ... 14 \n4.5.3.3 EEA Levels ... 15 \n4.5.3.4 Load Shed Obligation………………………………………………………………..20 \n4.5.3.5 EEA Termination…………………………………………...……………………….21 \n4.6 Black Start Service ... 21 \n4.6.1 Principles ... 22 \n4.6.2 Strategies ... 22 \n4.6.3 Priorities ... 23 \n4.6.4 Responsibilities ... 24 \n4.6.5 Black Start Emergency Back Up Communication Facilities Criteria ... 27 \n4.7 Geomagnetic Disturbance Operating Plan ... 28 \n4.7.1 Monitoring and Dissemination of Space Weather Information ... 28 \n4.7.2 Development and Submission of TO GMD Operating Procedures or Processes ... 28 \n4.7.3 ERCOT’s GMD Operating Plan and ERCOT Review of TO GMD Operating Procedures or \nProcesses ... 29 \n4.8 Responsive Reserve Service During Scarcity Conditions…………………………………………29 \n4.8.1 Responsive Reserve Service Manual Deployment…………………………………………..30 \n4.8.2 Responsive Reserve Service Manual Recall…….……….………….………………………30 \n5 Network Operations Modeling Requirements ... 1 \n5.1 System Modeling Information ... 1 \n6 Disturbance Monitoring and System Protection ... 1 \n6.1 Disturbance Monitoring Requirements ... 1 \n6.1.1",
      "highlights": [
